section(id='wireframe' class="container-fluid")
  div(class="section-wrapper row justify-content-md-center")
    h2(class='section-title col-lg-8 col-md-10') WIREFRAME
    div(class='gray-bg container-fluid')
      div(class='row justify-content-md-center')
        div(class='col-lg-12 ver-hor-center')
          img(src="/public/assets/version1.png", alt="")
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      For the 1st version, our team assumed that displayed all the functions in one page could help users fast navigate our app and save more clicking steps.
      All functions showed at the same time, so users could feel more comfortable to plan their trip.
    h3(class='section-sub-title col-lg-8 col-md-10') 1. Valuable but confusing
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      After we did a user testing, we found out 86% of users felt so confused about the planning page, indicating that it was too welcoming to check everything in one page. It was likely that planning pages contained so much information that users might feel lost and confused, and they ended up leaving our site entirely.
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      Like "Create New" and "Use This Plan" buttons,  they have different meanings. However, they showed at the same time in the plan preview page for various purposes. They could not indicate how the features work.
    h3(class='section-sub-title col-lg-8 col-md-10') 2. Useful but Low Usage
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      a. A few users started a new plan instead of using others' idea. The suggestion would show up in the empty planning page to help save time for POI exploration. However, limited information didn't look appealing to users.
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      b. Users expected a lot about the map. However, because of the limited space, the map looks too small to display the routes. It is a handy function, but the size makes it useless.

    div(id='version-2-img' class='gray-bg container-fluid')
      div(class='row justify-content-md-center')
        div(class='col-lg-12 ver-hor-center')
          img(src="/public/assets/Version2.png", alt="")
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      According to the problems we figured out from the previous version, we redesigned the planning pages.
    h3(class='section-sub-title col-lg-8 col-md-10') 1. Valuable but confusing
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      We separated the planning page into "Planning Pub" and "Planning Detail". The page layout and hierarchy are more precise than before. Plan preview(others plan) and planning(personal) are two individual pages, although they have the same layout.
    h3(class='section-sub-title col-lg-8 col-md-10') 2. Useful but Low Usage
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      a. Change the layout for the suggestions and visualize the data to catch users' eyes.
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      b. Full-screen map with a detailed route can provide more information for the users.

section(id='more-exploration' class="container-fluid")
  div(class="section-wrapper row justify-content-md-center")
    h2(class='section-title col-lg-8 col-md-10') MORE EXPLORATION
    div(class='gray-bg container-fluid')
      div(class='row justify-content-md-center')
        div(class='col-lg-12 ver-hor-center')
          img(src="/public/assets/MoreExploration.png", alt="")
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      When we complete version 2, we did another user testing with our target audiences. The majority of them had no confused at all, and they said this planning function is easy to use. Except the planning hub page did not show much information, and it looked pretty empty. Although we got significant progress for our app, we decided to do more explorations on the planning hub page.
    div(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10 info-list')
      p.
        Here is the information we can use for the hub page
      ul(class='no-style-ul')
        li
          p -Daily routes(need a bigger map)
        li
          p -City itineraries(Visualization)
        li
          p -Dates, weathers, locations, etc.(Basic information)
        li
          p -Trip summary(Visualization)
        li
          p -POI(Visualization)
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      After presenting my design explorations with other designers and engineers, I found out that big images and icons simplify the information.  Visualization summary could help increase user engagement. Generally, the pictured itinerary list became a winning experiment.
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      I decided to use a foldable design to avoid any visual noise so that users would engage more easily with the daily card. Moreover, it also left more space for the suggestion.

section(id='final-design' class="container-fluid")
  div(class="section-wrapper row justify-content-md-center")
    h2(class='section-title col-lg-8 col-md-10') FINAL DESIGN
    div(class='gray-bg container-fluid')
      div(class='row justify-content-md-center')
        div(class='col-lg-12 ver-hor-center')
          img(src="/public/assets/final.jpg", alt="")
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      "Planning hub" and "Planning Detail" are sharing different functions, which make the planning process more organized. Visualized itineraries are more appealing to users. Adequate information not only fills the white space but also improves the engagement with users.  It decreases the possibility of misunderstanding and confusing, and the users won't need time to learn while they are planning the trips.
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      A.I. trip suggestion is one of the most prominent advantages of our platform. Users must be comfortable to access the suggestions from our system. This new design increases the click rate for users to check the recommendations.

